{
  "texts": [
    "If this is right, we pick out the elements of the formal order of an action (A)-(E) and the purely non-agential events these are supposed to correspond to, based on our prior understanding of the goal-directed structure of the whole action.",
    "Synthese (2025) 205:47",
    "Anscombe's point here can be easy to miss.",
    "Since a basic grasp of this structure is part of the manifestly experienced reality of anyone \"grown to reason\" in a world populated by practically rational agents (2000, p. 8), someone in this position might take for granted the conceptual background required for picking out actions as actions.",
    "This might lead them to assume that passive-voice event descriptions derived from these correspond to an order in events that could in principle be parsed independently of it."
  ]
}